{"title_page": "Laird & Company", "text_new": "{{short description|Distillery}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2014}}\n[[File:Jack Rose Cocktail.jpg|thumb|300px|Laird\u2019s Applejack Bottles|alt=]]\n'''Laird & Company''' is a beverage alcohol company located in the Scobeyvillle section of Colts Neck Township, New Jersey.\u00a0Founded by Robert Laird in 1780.\u00a0It is the oldest licensed distillery in continuous operation, except during prohibition, in the United States. Robert Laird served in the Continental Army under George Washington.\u00a0Washington asked Laird for his \u201ccyder spirits\u201d recipe after the revolution.\u00a0 \u00a0Laird & Company holds federal distillation and importer licenses and a rectifier blender license from the New Jersey Division of Alcoholic Beverage Control. \n\nThe distillation of the company\u2019s flagship product, Laird\u2019s Applejack, uses apples from central Virginia at the company\u2019s plant in North Garden, Virginia.\u00a0The apple brandy barrels are then shipped to the Scobeyville, New Jersey plant for ageing.\u00a0All blending, rectification and bottling is done at the company headquarters in Scobyeville, New Jersey. In addition to Laird\u2019s Applejack, Laird & Company offers a wide range of domestic and imported spirts and wines.\u00a0\n\nLaird & Company is the oldest licensed distillery in continuous operation, except during prohibition, in the United States.\n\n<br />\n\n==See also==\n* [[Alcohol laws of New Jersey]]\n* [[List of wineries, breweries, and distilleries in New Jersey]]\n* [[New Jersey wine]]\n* [[New Jersey distilled spirits]]\n* [[New Jersey Division of Alcoholic Beverage Control]]\n* [[Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.lairdandcompany.com Laird & Company] (business website)\n\n{{New Jersey Wineries, Breweries, and Distilleries}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Laird and Company}}\n[[Category:Distilleries in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:American distilled drinks]]\n[[Category:Colts Neck Township, New Jersey]]\n\n{{NewJersey-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Distillery}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2014}}\n[[File:Jack Rose Cocktail.jpg|thumb|right|300px|A \"Jack Rose\" cocktail is made from Applejack and Grenadine.]]\n'''Laird & Company''' is a beverage alcohol company located in the Scobeyvillle section of Colts Neck Township, New Jersey.\u00a0Founded by Robert Laird in 1780.\u00a0It is the oldest licensed distillery in continuous operation, except during prohibition, in the United States. Robert Laird served in the Continental Army under George Washington.\u00a0Washington asked Laird for his \u201ccyder spirits\u201d recipe after the revolution.\u00a0 \u00a0Laird & Company holds federal distillation and importer licenses and a rectifier blender license from the New Jersey Division of Alcoholic Beverage Control. \n\nThe distillation of the company\u2019s flagship product, Laird\u2019s Applejack, uses apples from central Virginia at the company\u2019s plant in North Garden, Virginia.\u00a0The apple brandy barrels are then shipped to the Scobeyville, New Jersey plant for ageing.\u00a0All blending, rectification and bottling is done at the company headquarters in Scobyeville, New Jersey. In addition to Laird\u2019s Applejack, Laird & Company offers a wide range of domestic and imported spirts and wines.\u00a0\n\nLaird & Company is the oldest licensed distillery in continuous operation, except during prohibition, in the United States.\n\n<br />\n\n==See also==\n* [[Alcohol laws of New Jersey]]\n* [[List of wineries, breweries, and distilleries in New Jersey]]\n* [[New Jersey wine]]\n* [[New Jersey distilled spirits]]\n* [[New Jersey Division of Alcoholic Beverage Control]]\n* [[Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.lairdandcompany.com Laird & Company] (business website)\n\n{{New Jersey Wineries, Breweries, and Distilleries}}\n\n{{